<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2362] Improve gets/scans when all columns of a key is requested.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2362</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now, we get one KeyValue at a time and run it through the matcher even if the query is to fetch the entire row (or even an entire column family for a key). This causes the blocks to be fetched serially from HDFS. We can optimize this by looking at the block map, and fetching all the blocks spanned by the key in one request to HDFS.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
